The 2-hour movie format is built for different storytelling compared to a 6-hour mini-series format that Marvel follows for its TV shows. The magic of the previous phases was in the gaps between each outing - the viewers could fill those voids in their heads on their own.

Phase 4 MCU movies will feel underwhelming because they will always come up short against the depth of character exploration in the new Marvel TV shows (especially Loki and Wandavision). In isolation, Dr Strange 2 was a fun and quirky ride. But it's a letdown post Wandavision.

Now we have these beautiful arcs on TV. And they are splendid - far richer and meatier. They are not fillers (Moon Knight for example) and stand on their own. 

But MCU films and TV has started feeling like completing a jigsaw from pieces of two different sets. It doesn't work.
